89 634 :M
(the main window. Also, subset windows cannot be iconified separately, but)S
89 647 :M
(disappear together with the associated main window when it is iconified.)S
89 672 :M
(A main window can have more than one associated subset window.)S
89 697 :M
(Subset windows have a menu slightly different from the menu of a main)S
89 710 :M
(window. Instead of the )S
212 710 :M
f1_12 sf
(File)S
f4_12 sf
( menu, subset windows have a )S
400 710 :M
f1_12 sf
(Subset)S
440 710 :M
f4_12 sf
( menu,)S
89 723 :M
(which has much less functionality. Subsets cannot be saved to or loaded from)S
89 736 :M
(disk files. However, they can be transferred to files indirectly, by cutting and)S
89 749 :M
(pasting subset contents into a main window and then saving the main window)S
89 762 :M
(contents.)S
